# SIP (RFC 3261, udp:5060) REGISTER request. Text message with Via/Max-Forwards/From/To/Call-ID/CSeq/
# Content-Length headers, CRLF line endings. The whole message is kept verbatim (byte-perfect); the
# start line is parsed for display. source: standard SIP REGISTER via a real UDP socket to 127.0.0.1:5060
# on a debian:12 container's ethernet lo, captured with tcpdump.

